entries.meaning: A form of romantic courtship typically between two individuals with the aim of assessing the other's suitability as a partner in an intimate relationship or as a spouse.
examples: Janet was surprised at how much casual dating had changed since she was last single.
We met on a popular dating app.

entries.meaning: An estimation of the age of an artifact, biological vestige, linguistic usage, etc.
examples: A comparison in seven sequoias between very careful counting and accurate dating in 2,000 years shows an average counting error of 35 years, which is only 1.7 per cent.

entries.meaning: The setting of a date on which an event or transaction is to take place or take effect.
examples: But C.O.D. datings are relatively rare. They are so disliked by buyers that they are used by sellers only when the latter are quite uncertain of a buyer's ability and willingness to pay.
